translit. mu, ma.

<xa>牟呼栗多</xa>muhūrta, the thirtieth part of an ahorātra, a day-and-night, i. e.

forty-eight minutes; a brief space of time,
moment; also (wrongly) a firm mind.

<xa>牟呼洛</xa>mahoraga, boa-demons, v. 摩睺.

<xa>牟娑</xa>(or 摩娑 or 目娑 ) (牟娑羅); 牟娑洛 (牟娑洛揭婆); 摩沙羅; 謨薩羅 or 牟薩羅 musāragalva, a kind of

