pearl; it is one of the 七寳 sapta ratna
q. v.

<xa>牟尼</xa>(牟尼仙), 文尼; 茂泥; (馬曷摩尼) 摩尼 muni; mahāmuni; 月摩尼 vimuni. A sage, saint, ascetic,

<pb n="225"/>
monk, especially Śākyamuni; interpreted as 寂 retired,
secluded, silent,

solitary, i. e. withdrawn from the world.
