the eighth century A. D. who is known as a
great opponent of Buddhism.

<xa>商諾迦縛婆</xa>(商諾縛婆) ; 商那和修; 舍那和修 (or 舍那波私) Sanakavisa; Sanavasa; a younger brother of

Ānanda. Also an arhat, whom Eitel gives as
