<xa>跋塀</xa>; 跋移; 末利.

<xa>婆羅</xa>pāla; keeper, guardian, warden; vihārapāla, warden of a monastery.
bala;

power, strength, especially the 五力 five
powers, pañca bālani, i.e. 五根; also the

<xa>十力</xa>daśabala, ten powers. Name of the sister of Ānanda who offered milk
<pb n="955"/>
to

Śākyamuni. bāla; 'young,' 'immature,'
