without the Buddha-truth.

<xa>貪</xa>rāga; colouring, dyeing, tint, red; affection, passion, vehement
longing or

desire; cf. M. W. In Chinese: cupidity,
desire; intp. tainted by and in bondage

<pb n="58"/>
to the five desires; it is the first in
