<xa>貪使</xa>(貪欲使) The messenger, or temptation of desire.

<xa>貪恚痴</xa>v. 貪欲瞋恚愚痴, 貪瞋痴.

<xa>貪惜</xa>To begrudge; be unwilling to give.

<xa>貪愛</xa>Desire, cupidity.

<xa>貪染</xa>The taint of desire, or greed.

<xa>貪欲</xa>Desire for and love of (the things of this life).

<xa>貪欲卽是道</xa>Desire is part of the universal law, and may be used for leading
